data_summary:
This data set provides an indication of cold-water fisheries productivity as per the ranges detailed in the Description.

- Blue Ribbon Streams: stream reaches with greater than or equal to 600 pounds of trout per stream mile;

- Red Ribbon Streams: stream reaches with between 300 - 599 pounds of trout per stream mile;

- Yellow Ribbon Streams: stream reaches with between 50 - 299 pounds of trout per stream mile;

- Green Ribbon Streams: stream reaches with between 1 - 49 pounds of trout per stream mile;

- Orange Ribbon Streams are indicative of any cool or warm water game fish presence

- Clear (black): stream reaches absent any color indicate no trout are present;

- Brown: reserved and not currently in use as a stream classification indicator
